name: language_html_data_fullwidth_angle_element
description: |
  Fullwidth angle brackets are not HTML delimiters, but NFKC normalization maps
  them to ASCII less-than and greater-than. Normalizing after validation and
  before HTML insertion can therefore turn this inert-looking text into the
  paired custom-element markup.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: utf8
unicode-meta:
  code-units: 18
  code-points: 14
  scalar-values: 14
  legacy-grapheme-clusters: 14
  extended-grapheme-clusters: 14
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "utf8"
  - "fullwidth"
  - "angle-bracket"
  - "nfkc"
  - "normalization"
  - "inert-canary"
---
＜x-xss-canary＞
